Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.93,0:00:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,180)}{\fs22\fsp5\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(1600,1000)}{\blur4}{\t(0,1600,\blur0)}{\t(0,0,\fs18)}地球脉动{\fs20\fsp2}III
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.93,0:00:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,200)}{\fs10\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(2400,560)}第 二 集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.27,0:00:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of our planet still remains unexplored...\N{\rEng}我们星球上的很多地区仍未被探索
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.72,0:00:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for most of it is covered by water.\N{\rEng}因为这些地区大部分都被水覆盖
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.67,0:01:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Every journey below the surface can reveal something extraordinary.\N{\rEng}每一次水中之旅都能揭开奇妙事物的面纱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.91,0:01:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,More than a thousand new species are discovered here every year.\N{\rEng}在这里 每年有超过一千种新物种被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.83,0:01:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The ocean is home to 80% of all animal life on Planet Earth.\N{\rEng}海洋是地球上80%动物的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, thriving in this varied world\N{\rEng}但如今 要在这个多变的世界中生存发展
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.64,0:01:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes demands the most surprising behaviour.\N{\rEng}有时需要做出令人惊讶的行为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.57,0:02:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,185)}{\fs25\fsp\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(2400,560)}波 涛 之 下
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.47,0:02:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The shallow seas of the tropics.\N{\rEng}热带浅海
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.71,0:02:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This may look like a paradise...\N{\rEng}这里看上去如天堂般美好
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but beneath the surface, it is an arena\N{\rEng}但海面之下 是一个
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.63,0:02:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for constant life-and-death struggles,\N{\rEng}不断进行生死搏斗的竞技场
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.03,0:02:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where not everything is quite as it seems.\N{\rEng}隐藏在表面现象背后
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.84,0:02:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A predatory lionfish...\N{\rEng}掠食性狮子鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:03:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on the hunt for shrimp and small fish.\N{\rEng}正在寻找小虾小鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With so many places for its prey to hide,\N{\rEng}有这么多地方可供猎物藏身
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the lionfish has to be patient.\N{\rEng}狮子鱼必须耐心下来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This shrimp appears tempting.\N{\rEng}这只虾看起来很诱人
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As the lion-fish closes in,\N{\rEng}当狮子鱼靠近时
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it fans out its fins to disorientate its prey.\N{\rEng}它会展开鳍来迷惑猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The hunter becomes the hunted.\N{\rEng}猎人变成了猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.07,0:04:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tricked by one of the shallow sea's most extraordinary predators...\N{\rEng}被浅海中最特别的捕食者之一摆了一道
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.19,0:04:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a clown frogfish!\N{\rEng}大斑躄鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,On its head, it carries a fishing rod –\N{\rEng}它头上带着一根鱼竿
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a modified dorsal fin,\N{\rEng}是一种改良后的背鳍
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.24,0:04:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,baited with a lure - easily mistaken for a shrimp.\N{\rEng}诱饵很容易被误认为是一只虾
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.75,0:04:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But, when the fish stop biting,\N{\rEng}但鱼都不上钩时
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.47,0:04:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's time to pack the rod away\N{\rEng}就该把鱼竿收起来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.07,0:04:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and move on.\N{\rEng}换个地方了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.35,0:04:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And, for a frogfish, that takes time.\N{\rEng}对于躄鱼来说 这得花不少时间
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.71,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than swim, frogfish walk!\N{\rEng}躄鱼不会游泳 反而只会走路
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Its fins have, in effect, become feet.\N{\rEng}它的鳍实际上相当于脚
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.27,0:05:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not look pretty,\N{\rEng}躄鱼可能看起来不漂亮
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.20,0:05:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but what appears to be coral living on its skin is actually camouflage.\N{\rEng}但看似长在它身上的珊瑚实际上是一种伪装
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As every good angler knows,\N{\rEng}每个钓鱼高手都知道
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,picking the right spot is important.\N{\rEng}地点非常重要
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.80,0:05:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jigging the rod sends out pressure waves\N{\rEng}摇动钓竿发出震动
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:06:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to attract the attention of possible prey.\N{\rEng}从而吸引猎物的注意
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,These dragonets are certainly interested.\N{\rEng}这些鳜鱼被吸引住了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there.\N{\rEng}还差一步
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hook, line, and sinker.\N{\rEng}彻底上钩了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.66,0:07:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Like all shallow seas, the cold waters off the coast of North America,\N{\rEng}浅海往往受益于强烈的阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.91,0:07:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,benefit from the intensity of the sunshine.\N{\rEng}北美沿岸的冷水域也不例外
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, that fuels\N{\rEng}在这里 阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.68,0:07:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the fastest-growing organisms on the planet...\N{\rEng}为地球上生长最快的生物之一提供了物质基础
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,giant kelp.\N{\rEng}巨藻
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.91,0:07:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Towering forests can eventually reach the height\N{\rEng}高耸的巨藻森林最终可以达到
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of a 12-storey building.\N{\rEng}12层楼的高度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,These forests are nurseries for young horn sharks.\N{\rEng}这些森林是幼年角鲨生长的温床
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.56,0:07:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As the sun begins to set,\N{\rEng}太阳落下时
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.73,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they leave their daytime shelter\N{\rEng}它们离开白天的庇护所
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.98,0:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and set off into the heart of the kelp forest to find food.\N{\rEng}前往巨藻森林中心寻找食物
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.75,0:08:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Barely half a metre long, this little shark is extremely vulnerable.\N{\rEng}这条只有半米长的鲨鱼非常脆弱
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There are monsters here.\N{\rEng}这里生活着巨兽
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A giant sea bass\N{\rEng}一条巨大的海鲈
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.12,0:08:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,weighing over 200kg...\N{\rEng}重达200公斤以上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and wolf-eels, with big teeth\N{\rEng}以及长着巨大牙齿的狼鳗
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.92,0:08:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that can crush little red sea urchins.\N{\rEng}能够咬碎小红海胆
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.69,0:08:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But the biggest danger comes from other sharks -\N{\rEng}但最大的危险来自其他鲨鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.47,0:08:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,houndsharks...\N{\rEng}皱唇鲨
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.14,0:09:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and huge broadnose sevengills.\N{\rEng}以及巨大的扁头哈那鲨
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In this forest, it pays to keep a low profile.\N{\rEng}在这片森林中 最好是保持低调
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel shark...\N{\rEng}扁鲨
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the most deadly sharks in the kelp forest,\N{\rEng}巨藻森林中最危险的鲨鱼之一
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly the best camouflaged.\N{\rEng}也有着最高明的伪装
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.71,0:10:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel shark will lie in wait for days...\N{\rEng}扁鲨通常会潜伏数天
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.03,0:10:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but this one has already attracted too much attention.\N{\rEng}但这条扁鲨已经吸引了太多的注意
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.42,0:10:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not welcome here.\N{\rEng}这里不欢迎他
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.79,0:10:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the coast is clear.\N{\rEng}现在 危险解除
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.43,0:11:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But angel sharks hunt around the clock.\N{\rEng}但扁鲨是全天候捕猎
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.31,0:11:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Openings for breathing, called spiracles,\N{\rEng}呼吸孔
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.94,0:11:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,blow out sand that helps cover its body.\N{\rEng}可以吹起沙子以掩藏身体
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The trap is set.\N{\rEng}陷阱已经布好
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.99,0:11:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying close to the seabed is a good way to avoid most predators.\N{\rEng}贴紧海底是躲避大多数捕食者的好办法
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.47,0:12:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster than the blink of an eye.\N{\rEng}迅雷不及掩耳
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.06,0:12:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not over yet.\N{\rEng}但还没完
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Horn sharks have a secret weapon.\N{\rEng}角鲨有一种秘密武器
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.63,0:13:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharp spikes keep them very much off the menu for most.\N{\rEng}锋利的尖刺使它们得以幸免于大多数捕食者
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.44,0:13:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this young horn shark can hunt in safety...\N{\rEng}因此 这条年轻的角鲨可以安全地捕猎
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for now.\N{\rEng}最起码暂时安全
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.83,0:14:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Violent winter storms batter these kelp forests.\N{\rEng}猛烈的冬季风暴扑向了这片巨藻森林
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.07,0:14:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The plants can be ripped from the seafloor...\N{\rEng}这些植物会被连根拔起
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.19,0:14:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and carried away far out to sea.\N{\rEng}被海浪带向远处
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.65,0:14:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The open ocean is a vast, featureless desert.\N{\rEng}开阔的海洋是一片广袤无奇的沙漠
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a small piece of drifting kelp can become valuable.\N{\rEng}哪怕是一小片漂浮的海藻也会变得弥足珍贵
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.59,0:15:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just what these fish have been searching for.\N{\rEng}这正是这群鱼一直在寻找的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, shelter where eggs can be laid unobtrusively is rare...\N{\rEng}在这里 不引人注目的产卵处十分稀少
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.27,0:15:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so they make the most of it.\N{\rEng}因此要充分利用
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.99,0:15:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Each female produces up to a thousand eggs,\N{\rEng}每条雌性产下多达一千颗卵
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the males rush in to fertilise them.\N{\rEng}雄性争先恐后使鱼卵受精
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All this activity attracts the attention of blue sharks.\N{\rEng}这些活动吸引了大青鲨的注意
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.35,0:15:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They can travel thousands of miles\N{\rEng}它们为了寻找食物
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.99,0:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,through the ocean in search of food...\N{\rEng}可以在海中移动数千里
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.98,0:15:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they may not have eaten for weeks.\N{\rEng}而且这些大青鲨可能已经几周没吃过东西了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that they're in luck.\N{\rEng}似乎走运了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But these fish are no easy meal.\N{\rEng}但这些鱼并不好抓
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.63,0:16:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They are flying fish!\N{\rEng}它们可是飞鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue shark, however,\N{\rEng}然而这条大青鲨
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.99,0:17:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are not here for the fish...\N{\rEng}不是奔着鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they have come for the caviar.\N{\rEng}而是奔着鱼子来的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But flying fish lay so many eggs,\N{\rEng}但飞鱼群产下的卵非常多
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.73,0:17:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that the sharks' feasts hardly make an impact.\N{\rEng}多到鲨鱼的盛宴几乎不会造成影响
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in a few months' time, a new generation will take to the skies.\N{\rEng}几个月后 新一代飞鱼又将在空中"展翅"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.19,0:18:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Floating islands of weed are always attractive to creatures\N{\rEng}对于在大海中寻找居所的生物来说
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.98,0:18:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for shelter out in the big blue.\N{\rEng}漂浮的水草总是很有吸引力
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But, in today's ocean, they are being replaced by something else...\N{\rEng}然而如今的海洋中 取代水草浮岛的是
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,plastic.\N{\rEng}塑料
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,12 million tons of it end up in the ocean every year.\N{\rEng}每年有1200万吨塑料最终流入海洋
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The deadliest kind are discarded fishing lines and nets.\N{\rEng}最致命的是废弃的渔线渔网
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Each year, it's likely over half a million animals are ensnared\N{\rEng}每年 约有50多万只动物
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed by these "ghost nets."\N{\rEng}被这些"幽灵网"困住并死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.98,0:19:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But some animals are learning\N{\rEng}但有些动物在学习
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.36,0:19:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,how to take advantage of the plastic rafts...\N{\rEng}如何利用这些塑料筏
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.39,0:19:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and use them for shelter, or even as a home.\N{\rEng}将其作为庇护所 甚至作为家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.91,0:19:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This male Columbus crab – barely bigger than your thumb nail –\N{\rEng}这只和拇指指甲差不多大的雄性哥伦布蟹
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.03,0:19:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is a castaway.\N{\rEng}漂泊无归
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.35,0:19:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinging to his net,\N{\rEng}它紧紧抓着网
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.06,0:19:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he may have been drifting on ocean currents for months.\N{\rEng}可能已经在洋流中漂流了数月
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.00,0:19:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, fully grown, he needs to find a partner.\N{\rEng}如今它已经长大了 需要找个伴侣
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But where?\N{\rEng}但哪儿找呢
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.23,0:20:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly not here,\N{\rEng}肯定不是这儿
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,alone on the net.\N{\rEng}这儿只有它孤零零一个
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Columbus crabs are not good swimmers, so this male is marooned.\N{\rEng}哥伦布蟹并不擅长游泳 因此这只雄蟹走投无路
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.43,0:20:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps a passing loggerhead turtle could be the chance to hitch a lift.\N{\rEng}也许一只路过的红海龟是个搭便车的好机会
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.79,0:21:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Made it!\N{\rEng}成功抵达
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.11,0:21:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's more than one passenger here -\N{\rEng}可这里还有别的乘客
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.43,0:21:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a female Columbus crab!\N{\rEng}一只雌哥伦布蟹
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.00,0:21:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They waste no time in getting acquainted...\N{\rEng}它们决定不浪费时间熟悉彼此
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.23,0:22:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and start to mate.\N{\rEng}而是直接开始交配
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.35,0:22:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This pair may well stay together for the rest of their lives.\N{\rEng}这对哥伦布蟹很可能会一起度过余生
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.95,0:22:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A turtle, after all, makes an excellent home.\N{\rEng}毕竟 海龟身上是个完美的家
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.91,0:22:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In return, the crabs provide an onboard grooming service.\N{\rEng}作为回报 哥伦布蟹会提供甲板清洁服务
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.76,0:23:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Finding a partner in the vast ocean is not easy.\N{\rEng}在广袤的海洋中寻找伴侣并不容易
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.91,0:23:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn in the Sea of Cortez...\N{\rEng}科提兹海 黎明之际
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.23,0:23:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobula rays.\N{\rEng}蝠鲼
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.87,0:24:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gathering here, most likely to breed.\N{\rEng}它们聚集于此 很可能是为了进行繁育
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.55,0:24:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No-one is sure why they leap,\N{\rEng}蝠鲼跃出海面的原因尚不清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but the loud splashes certainly seem to attract more rays.\N{\rEng}但水花飞溅的声音显然吸引来了更多的同胞
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.47,0:24:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Other creatures, however, are also listening.\N{\rEng}然而 听到声音的还有其他生物
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.02,0:24:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Orca have heard the splashes.\N{\rEng}虎鲸循声而来
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.91,0:25:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This female specialises in hunting rays.\N{\rEng}这头雌性虎鲸精通蝠鲼狩猎
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.47,0:25:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, she is teaching two youngsters\N{\rEng}但今天 它正在传授两头年轻虎鲸
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.31,0:25:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the finer points of Mobula ray hunting.\N{\rEng}狩猎蝠鲼的细节诀窍
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.19,0:25:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The rays are fast and can outmanoeuvre an orca.\N{\rEng}蝠鲼的速度很快 甚至快于虎鲸
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.95,0:26:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows she needs to herd the prey into a tight group...\N{\rEng}雌虎鲸明白它需要将猎物驱赶到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.64,0:26:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but she can't do that on her own.\N{\rEng}但这项工作无法独自完成
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.16,0:26:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It will take teamwork,\N{\rEng}而是需要团队合作
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.18,0:26:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is today's lesson.\N{\rEng}而这正是这节课的主题
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.68,0:26:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The young orca are quick to catch on.\N{\rEng}年轻的虎鲸理解的很快
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.83,0:26:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The rays are surrounded.\N{\rEng}蝠鲼群被包围了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.91,0:26:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They dive...\N{\rEng}它们迅速下潜
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.07,0:26:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,only to be forced back up again by the experienced female.\N{\rEng}却被经验丰富的雌虎鲸逼回海面
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.95,0:27:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, with the exhausted rays trapped against the surface,\N{\rEng}精疲力竭的蝠鲼无路可逃
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.24,0:27:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,she attacks...\N{\rEng}雌虎鲸发动进攻
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.54,0:27:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the young ones follow her lead.\N{\rEng}年轻虎鲸则紧跟它的脚步
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.62,0:27:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This family are the only orca known to hunt rays like this...\N{\rEng}这一家子是已知的虎鲸群中 唯一用这种方式捕猎蝠鲼的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.03,0:27:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are lethally efficient.\N{\rEng}而且效率十分之高
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.99,0:27:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But it appears that school is over for today.\N{\rEng}但似乎今天的课程到此为止了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.27,0:27:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For a few battle-scarred survivors,\N{\rEng}这些幸存下来的伤痕累累的蝠鲼
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.95,0:27:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a lucky reprieve.\N{\rEng}可以暂时喘一口气了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.95,0:28:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,With the orca gone, the rays can resume their courtship...\N{\rEng}虎鲸离开后 蝠鲼群得以继续它们的求偶行为
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.11,0:28:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they do so in astounding numbers.\N{\rEng}而且规模惊人
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.09,0:28:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Tens of thousands of rays in a single shoal.\N{\rEng}数以万计的蝠鲼聚集在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.71,0:28:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Vast areas of our ocean are yet to be explored.\N{\rEng}海洋中还有广阔的区域尚未探索
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.67,0:29:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The least known parts of it are its great depths.\N{\rEng}这之中最不为人知的区域是海洋深处
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.55,0:29:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Only highly-specialised vessels can take you there.\N{\rEng}只有高度专业化的潜艇才能抵达
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.15,0:29:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As you descend, the sunlight rapidly fades.\N{\rEng}随着越潜越深 阳光会迅速减弱
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.91,0:29:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,200m down, you enter the twilight zone...\N{\rEng}200米深处 是一片黄昏世界
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.87,0:29:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,an alien world, inhabited by creatures beyond imagination.\N{\rEng}仿佛置身外星 超乎想象的生物生存于此
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.79,0:30:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A siphonophore,with a cloak of lethal stinging tentacles.\N{\rEng}管水母 身披一层致命的刺触须
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.83,0:30:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Siphonophores repeatedly clone themselves\N{\rEng}管水母反复地自我复制
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.91,0:30:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and so grow to immense lengths.\N{\rEng}不断生长 体长极长
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.46,0:30:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This one measures 45m and is the longest animal ever recorded.\N{\rEng}这一只达到了45米 是有记录以来所有动物中最长的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.10,0:30:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With such deadly predators around,\N{\rEng}附近存在着如此致命的捕食者
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.49,0:31:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,creatures here go to great lengths to hide.\N{\rEng}这里的生物因此不遗余力地隐藏自己
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.70,0:31:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A glass squid...\N{\rEng}玻璃鱿鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.78,0:31:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,completely transparent,\N{\rEng}身体完全透明
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.59,0:31:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,except for its eyes...\N{\rEng}除了眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.51,0:31:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and stomach,\N{\rEng}以及胃部
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.82,0:31:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so it is extremely difficult to find in the gloom.\N{\rEng}因此它很难在黑暗中被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.04,0:31:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 1,000m,\N{\rEng}1000米深处以下
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.94,0:31:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,all traces of sunlight have disappeared.\N{\rEng}一缕阳光也无法照射进来
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.91,0:32:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the midnight zone.\N{\rEng}一片午夜世界
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.75,0:32:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Catching food in the perpetual darkness is not easy.\N{\rEng}在永恒的黑暗中捕捉食物十分困难
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.31,0:32:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A gulper eel.\N{\rEng}吞鳗
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.79,0:32:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Its giant, extendable mouth\N{\rEng}它巨大且可伸展的嘴部
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.99,0:32:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,can engulf prey larger than its own body.\N{\rEng}可以吞下比自身还大的猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.83,0:33:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Two miles down, you finally reach the ocean floor.\N{\rEng}再往下三公里 终于抵达了洋底
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.63,0:33:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We know more about the surface of Mars.\N{\rEng}相比于此 我们对火星表面的了解还更多一些
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.44,0:33:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The pressure of the water is 300 times greater than at the surface...\N{\rEng}这里的水压是海面处的300倍
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.58,0:33:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's freezing cold.\N{\rEng}而且十分寒冷
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.43,0:33:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, amazingly, there are animals living here.\N{\rEng}然而令人惊奇的是 依然有动物生活于此
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.60,0:33:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Muusoctopus robustus,\N{\rEng}Muusoctopus robustus
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.60,0:34:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,nicknamed the pearl octopus.\N{\rEng}绰号珍珠章鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.88,0:34:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Breeding, in these extreme conditions poses\N{\rEng}在这样的极端条件下繁殖
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.63,0:34:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a particular problem for these animals.\N{\rEng}给这种动物带来了一个特殊的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.64,0:34:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At these low temperatures,\N{\rEng}在如此低温下
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.07,0:34:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this female's eggs could take over ten years to develop.\N{\rEng}雌性珍珠章鱼卵发育时间长达十数年之久
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.83,0:34:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So she travels to a very special place.\N{\rEng}因此它会前往一个特别的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.22,0:34:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the largest known gathering of octopus in the world.\N{\rEng}这是世上已知的最大规模的章鱼聚集群
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.53,0:35:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She joins 20,000 other females...\N{\rEng}它与其他两万只雌性珍珠章鱼一起
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.51,0:35:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all here to lay their eggs.\N{\rEng}来到这里产卵
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Water, heated deep in the Earth's crust,\N{\rEng}在地壳深处被加热的水
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.47,0:35:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,rises through cracks in the seabed...\N{\rEng}从海底的板块裂缝中涌出
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,raising the temperature to as much as 10 degrees Celsius.\N{\rEng}将温度升高至10摄氏度
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.18,0:35:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A deep-sea thermal spa!\N{\rEng}形成一片深海温泉
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.15,0:35:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This warmth significantly speeds up the development of their eggs.\N{\rEng}温暖的水显著加速了珍珠章鱼卵的发育
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.35,0:35:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, they will still take nearly two years to hatch.\N{\rEng}但尽管如此 小章鱼也需要近两年时间才能孵化出来
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.67,0:35:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a female is settled,\N{\rEng}一旦雌性珍珠章鱼安顿下来
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.11,0:36:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,she won't move from her spot...\N{\rEng}它便再也不会移动
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.15,0:36:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not even to feed.\N{\rEng}甚至不会进食
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.08,0:36:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She will constantly tend to her brood –\N{\rEng}它会一直照顾自己的孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.06,0:36:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping them clean,\N{\rEng}保持孩子们的清洁
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.13,0:36:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and oxygenating them with jets of water.\N{\rEng}以及使用水流为孩子供氧
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.51,0:36:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl octopus mothers must surely be amongst the most devoted.\N{\rEng}珍珠章鱼母亲是世上最无私奉献的母亲之一
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.95,0:36:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After almost two years, the ordeal take its toll.\N{\rEng}两年间 这份艰苦的工作对珍珠章鱼母亲的身体造成了严重的损伤
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.43,0:37:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But the vigil is almost over.\N{\rEng}但漫长的坚守也终于进入了尾声
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.99,0:38:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The last of the brood are gently encouraged to leave.\N{\rEng}珍珠章鱼母亲温和地鼓励最后一窝孩子走出家门
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.30,0:38:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But this will be a final act.\N{\rEng}这也用尽了它的最后一丝力量
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.11,0:38:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Like all the mothers here, this octopus is starved and exhausted.\N{\rEng}像每一只珍珠章鱼母亲一样 它已经饥寒交迫 精疲力竭
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.51,0:38:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Her life will soon be over.\N{\rEng}它的生命也走到了终点
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.51,0:38:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But this devotion means that her offspring are among\N{\rEng}但这样的无私奉献意味着它的后代
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.16,0:39:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the largest and most developed of any octopus\N{\rEng}将是所有章鱼中个头最大 发育最完善的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.10,0:39:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and have the best chance of survival\N{\rEng}将在严酷的深海世界中
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.59,0:39:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the demanding world of the deep.\N{\rEng}拥有最佳的生存机会
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.94,0:39:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finding more of these strange hot springs every year.\N{\rEng}每年我们都会发现更多这种奇异的热泉
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.15,0:39:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In some places, they can be astonishingly violent.\N{\rEng}在某些地方 热泉的剧烈程度相当惊人
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.63,0:39:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Super-heated water, hot enough to melt lead,\N{\rEng}足以融化铅的过热水
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.43,0:39:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,spouts from the seafloor.\N{\rEng}从海底喷涌而出
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.55,0:39:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dissolved minerals condense around them\N{\rEng}溶解的矿物质在热泉周围凝结
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.10,0:40:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to form towering chimneys, known as hydrothermal vents.\N{\rEng}形成高耸的烟囱状 被称为深海热液喷口
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.45,0:40:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They are home to unique communities of animals\N{\rEng}深海热液喷口是独特动物群落的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.03,0:40:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that all rely on the nutrients in the scalding water.\N{\rEng}这些动物依靠滚烫的水中的营养物质生存
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.11,0:40:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some suggest that vents like these could be the places\N{\rEng}有观点认为四十亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.95,0:40:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where life on Earth first began four billion years ago.\N{\rEng}生命正是起源于类似这样的喷口
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.13,0:40:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is now evidence of hydrothermal vents\N{\rEng}如今有证据表明 木星和土星的卫星上
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.27,0:40:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,on the moons of Jupiter and Saturn.\N{\rEng}同样存在热液喷口
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.16,0:40:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Could they too be supporting life?\N{\rEng}它们也能孕育生命吗
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:41:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here on Earth, the influence of these vents\N{\rEng}在地球上 这些喷口的影响范围
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.84,0:41:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,extends far beyond their chimneys.\N{\rEng}远远不止于烟囱周围
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.56,0:41:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The essential nutrients carried in these plumes\N{\rEng}烟雾中携带的基本营养物质
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.95,0:41:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can rise all the way to the surface two miles above.\N{\rEng}可以一直上升至三公里之上的海平面
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.26,0:41:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, they stimulate the rapid growth of tiny marine plants\N{\rEng}在这里 它们能极大的促进
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.96,0:41:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on an astronomic scale.\N{\rEng}微小海洋植物的生长
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.67,0:41:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This phytoplankton is so abundant\N{\rEng}大量的浮游植物
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.00,0:41:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that it produces half of all the oxygen on Earth.\N{\rEng}生产了地球上一半的氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.47,0:42:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also food for a host of minute animals \N{\rEng}浮游植物同时也是许多微小动物的食物
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.55,0:42:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,zooplankton.\N{\rEng}也就是浮游动物
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.63,0:42:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, they are the basis of the food chains\N{\rEng}它们共同构成了海洋中
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.24,0:42:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that sustain nearly all life in the ocean.\N{\rEng}几乎所有生命的食物链基础
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.04,0:42:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Pacific waters off South America,\N{\rEng}在南美洲附近的太平洋海域
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.48,0:42:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they feed anchovy that gather here in billions.\N{\rEng}它们是聚集在这里的数十亿条凤尾鱼的食物来源
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.78,0:42:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of the world's most productive ecosystems.\N{\rEng}这是世界上生产力最高的生态系统之一
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.60,0:43:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These South American sea lions are on the hunt.\N{\rEng}这些南美海狮正在捕猎
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.83,0:43:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But the anchovy shoal has already been located...\N{\rEng}但这里的凤尾鱼群已经被发现了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.35,0:43:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by the planet's most efficient hunters.\N{\rEng}被地球上最高效的捕猎者捷足先登
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.11,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A net, over half a mile long,\N{\rEng}一张近1公里长的渔网
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.87,0:43:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,encircles the shoal.\N{\rEng}将鱼群包围
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.68,0:43:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It can trap over a million fish.\N{\rEng}它能捕获超过一百万条鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.69,0:44:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sea lions aren't about to go hungry.\N{\rEng}但这些海狮是不会空着肚子的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.93,0:44:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They have learnt to look for holes in the net.\N{\rEng}它们学会了寻找渔网上的破洞
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.85,0:44:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why waste energy when food comes to you as easily as this?!\N{\rEng}这么容易就能填饱肚子 何必还费劲捕猎呢
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.12,0:44:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As more and more sea lions arrive,\N{\rEng}随着越来越多海狮的到来
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.33,0:44:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some change their tactics.\N{\rEng}一些海狮改变了策略
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.78,0:44:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They line up on both sides of the net...\N{\rEng}它们排列在渔网两侧
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.43,0:44:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and wait.\N{\rEng}然后静候佳音
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.94,0:45:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As the net tightens, the anchovy panic and rush for the surface.\N{\rEng}渔网收紧时 凤尾鱼惊慌失措 纷纷跃向水面
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.31,0:45:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the moment the sea lions have been waiting for.\N{\rEng}海狮等的就是这个时候
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.64,0:45:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such an effective way of hunting that the sea lions here\N{\rEng}这是一种非常高效的狩猎方式
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.41,0:45:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are changing their natural behaviour...\N{\rEng}这里的海狮正在改变它们天生的习性
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.35,0:45:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and are raiding the fishing nets\N{\rEng}成千上万的海狮聚集在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.16,0:45:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thousands.\N{\rEng}掠夺渔网中的凤尾鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.22,0:46:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,With the net almost drawn in,\N{\rEng}随着渔网被彻底收紧
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.54,0:46:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the fishermen beat out a warning signal.\N{\rEng}渔民们发出了警告信号
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.34,0:46:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is up.\N{\rEng}时间到了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.68,0:46:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the confusion, not everyone manages to escape.\N{\rEng}在混乱中 有些海狮没能成功逃脱
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.38,0:47:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The trapped sea lions are in danger of being drowned.\N{\rEng}被困在渔网中的海狮有被淹死的风险
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.67,0:47:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Pups are separated from their mothers.\N{\rEng}幼崽与母亲被迫分离
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.19,0:48:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at the last minute, the fishermen briefly drop their net...\N{\rEng}在最后一刻 渔民们短暂的松开了渔网
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.26,0:48:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the trapped sea lions can escape.\N{\rEng}被困海狮得以逃脱
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.71,0:48:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But many are not so lucky.\N{\rEng}然而幸运获救的只是少数
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.66,0:49:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, millions of animals are accidently caught\N{\rEng}世界范围内 每天数以百万计的动物
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.87,0:49:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and die in fishing nets every day.\N{\rEng}被渔网意外捕获并最终失去生命
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.35,0:49:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And this by-catch, as it's known,\N{\rEng}这种被称为副渔获物的意外捕获
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.92,0:49:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is pushing many species toward extinction.\N{\rEng}正在将许多物种推向灭绝的深渊
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.39,0:49:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Animals have evolved in remarkable ways\N{\rEng}动物以非凡的进化过程
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.79,0:49:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the demands of life in the ocean.\N{\rEng}逐渐适应了海洋生存环境
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.11,0:49:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But can they now adapt to the new challenge -\N{\rEng}然而如今面对新的挑战
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.32,0:49:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,living alongside us?\N{\rEng}它们能适应如何与人类共存吗
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.37,0:49:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(168,185)}{\fs22\2a&FF\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(255,0,255,0,400,4290,5290)}{\blur7}{\t(0,400,\blur0)}{\K40}幕
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.37,0:49:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(184,185)}{\fs22\2a&FF\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(255,0,255,400,800,4290,5290)}{\blur7}{\t(400,800,\blur0)}{\kt40\K40}后
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.37,0:49:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(200,185)}{\fs22\2a&FF\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(255,0,255,800,1200,4290,5290)}{\blur7}{\t(800,1200,\blur0)}{\kt80\K40}花
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.37,0:49:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(216,185)}{\fs22\2a&FF\bord0\blur0\shad0\fad(255,0,255,1200,1600,4290,5290)}{\blur7}{\t(1200,16 00,\blur0)}{\kt120\K40}絮
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.03,0:50:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The open ocean is home to some of the largest\N{\rEng}广袤的海洋是地球上一些最大的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.17,0:50:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and most extraordinary animals on Earth.\N{\rEng}最特别的动物的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.31,0:50:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But here, off the Canary Islands,\N{\rEng}但在这里 加那利群岛附近
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.55,0:50:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the Planet Earth team are searching for one of its smaller,\N{\rEng}「地球脉动」摄制组正在寻找海洋中一种体型较小
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.15,0:50:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and less familiar residents.\N{\rEng}不被人熟知的居民
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.79,0:50:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking for a tiny creature called a Columbus crab,\N{\rEng}我们在寻找一种叫哥伦布蟹的小生命
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.35,0:50:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which is only about the size of your thumbnail,\N{\rEng}只有拇指指甲大小
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.51,0:50:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which live on floating objects in the open ocean.\N{\rEng}生活在海上的漂浮物体上
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.19,0:50:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Columbus crabs were once only found on natural debris,\N{\rEng}哥伦布蟹曾经只能在天然漂浮物上发现
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.51,0:50:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,like driftwood or seaweed,\N{\rEng}比如浮木或者海藻上
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.59,0:50:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but the oceans are changing,\N{\rEng}但海洋一直在变化
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.63,0:50:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've been forced to adapt.\N{\rEng}它们不得不适应新的环境
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.83,0:50:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The best place to find Columbus crabs\N{\rEng}最容易从中找到哥伦布蟹的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.97,0:50:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in plastic\N{\rEng}是塑料
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.65,0:50:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because around 90% of the things we see drifting are plastic\N{\rEng}因为我们见到的漂浮物中有90%都是塑料
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.40,0:50:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most common items they find is discarded fishing gear.\N{\rEng}最多见的漂浮物是废弃渔具
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.14,0:50:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a million tons is left adrift in the ocean each year.\N{\rEng}每年有超过一百万吨渔具被丢弃到海洋中
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.79,0:51:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And Columbus crabs are now making their homes on these unnatural materials.\N{\rEng}哥伦布蟹如今正以这些人造物品为家
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.37,0:51:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\rEng}那儿有只蟹
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.63,0:51:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly, Columbus crabs are thriving on this new habitat.\N{\rEng}令人惊讶的是 哥伦布蟹在这些新家中发展蓬勃
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.15,0:51:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But, for larger ocean creatures, these nets can be lethal.\N{\rEng}但对于较大的海洋生物来说 废弃渔网有着致命危险
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.11,0:51:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Loggerhead sea turtles are especially vulnerable.\N{\rEng}红海龟尤其脆弱
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.56,0:51:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times, they are very injured\N{\rEng}很多时候它们会因此身受重伤
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.58,0:51:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and many times they don't even survive.\N{\rEng}甚至往往失去生命
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.83,0:51:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a sad situation.\N{\rEng}现状很不乐观
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.63,0:51:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As a rule, wildlife film-makers observe natural behaviour\N{\rEng}通常来说 野生纪录片团队只应观察生命的自然习性
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.63,0:51:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not interfere.\N{\rEng}而不应加以干涉
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.35,0:51:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is far from natural.\N{\rEng}但这已远非自然习性
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.67,0:52:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The team feel they must take action.\N{\rEng}摄制团队认为他们必须采取行动
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.47,0:52:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the turtle is quite OK.\N{\rEng}看起来这只海龟情况还好
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.83,0:52:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just finish to cut the plastic and then we release it.\N{\rEng}我们只需割开塑料 然后释放它
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.91,0:52:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bittersweet moment,\N{\rEng}这是一个苦乐参半的时刻
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.11,0:52:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as this is one of eight turtles they rescued whilst filming here.\N{\rEng}拍摄中救出的多达八只海龟 这仅是其中之一
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.35,0:52:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This situation is not natural,\N{\rEng}这种情况不是自然的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.67,0:52:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it's something that is being caused by human beings.\N{\rEng}而是人类造成的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.03,0:52:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, the crew now face dilemmas like this\N{\rEng}遗憾的是 摄制组不得不在多个拍摄地点中
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.47,0:53:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on many of their filming expeditions...\N{\rEng}面对类似的窘境
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.83,0:53:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,including, when they travelled to the Pacific coast of Chile,\N{\rEng}包括前往智利太平洋海岸
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.95,0:53:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to show how sea lions are competing for food with one of the biggest fisheries on Earth.\N{\rEng}拍摄海狮与地球上最大的渔场之一争夺食物的场景时
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.55,0:53:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Expedition leader Fernando Olivares takes the team to the fleet.\N{\rEng}队长费尔南多·奥里瓦雷斯带领团队前往捕鱼船队
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.51,0:53:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Diving near fishing nets is extremely dangerous,\N{\rEng}在渔网附近潜水是非常危险的
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.15,0:53:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so the crew must ensure they have the full cooperation of the fishermen.\N{\rEng}因此潜水团队必须确保得到渔民的全力配合
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.90,0:53:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Requesting permission to deploy divers outside the net?\N{\rEng}请求在渔网外部署潜水员
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.76,0:53:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that possible?\N{\rEng}情况允许吗
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.22,0:53:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Be extremely careful.\N{\rEng}允许 千万小心
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.74,0:53:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Captain.\N{\rEng}谢谢船长
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.03,0:54:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty hazardous place to dive.\N{\rEng}在这潜水相当危险
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.92,0:54:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a case of trying to keep an eye on the divers,\N{\rEng}这项工作需要时刻关注潜水员
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.95,0:54:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but the sea lions also like to go down and blow bubbles,\N{\rEng}但海狮也会潜下去呼出泡泡
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.89,0:54:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so you'll think you're following the divers,\N{\rEng}就有可能会发生你以为你跟着的是潜水员
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.61,0:54:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a sea lion will pop up.\N{\rEng}但其实是海狮的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.75,0:54:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking the utmost care,\N{\rEng}为了最大限度的确保安全
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.98,0:54:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the divers get a close-up view of the sheer scale of the operation.\N{\rEng}潜水员仔细观察了这次行动的规模
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.63,0:54:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This one net must have about 15 tons of fish in it\N{\rEng}这张渔网里准有15吨的鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.99,0:54:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's eight or nine boats in this one little bay,\N{\rEng}这个小海湾里有八到九艘船
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.11,0:54:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are just the small boats.\N{\rEng}这些只是些小船
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.79,0:54:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Out there, there are huge factory ships that are taking even bigger catches.\N{\rEng}在那边 有大船在执行更大规模的捕鱼任务
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.27,0:54:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How much fish a year from just here?\N{\rEng}这里一年能捕到多少鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.63,0:54:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From a million tons a year more or less.\N{\rEng}每年一百万吨上下
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.42,0:55:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The catches are so vast,\N{\rEng}捕鱼量如此之大
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.15,0:55:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the sea lions have changed their natural behaviour\N{\rEng}海狮已经改变了自然习性
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.27,0:55:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to collect anchovies directly from the nets.\N{\rEng}直接从渔网中捕捉凤尾鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.43,0:55:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a risky strategy.\N{\rEng}但这种方式存在风险
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.10,0:55:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The crew witnessed sea lions caught in nets multiple times.\N{\rEng}船员们多次目睹海狮被渔网捕获
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.15,0:55:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, it's intense mate, there are so many in there.\N{\rEng}太惨烈了 渔网里太多了
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.71,0:55:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a pup stuck in the net, calling to its mother,\N{\rEng}有一只海狮幼崽困在渔网里 一直在求助母亲
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.31,0:55:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and its mother's just on the outside of the net calling back.\N{\rEng}但母亲除了在渔网的另一侧呼叫也无能为力
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.63,0:55:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really hard to watch.\N{\rEng}真的很不忍心
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.75,0:55:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the pup's really panicking now.\N{\rEng}海狮幼崽现在很慌张
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.48,0:56:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, fishermen are able to release trapped sea lions...\N{\rEng}有时 渔民能够释放困住的海狮
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.35,0:56:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but not this time.\N{\rEng}但这次不行
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.83,0:56:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The pup is in serious danger.\N{\rEng}海狮幼崽命在顷刻
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.27,0:56:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, the crew decide to step in.\N{\rEng}摄制组再次决定采取行动
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.83,0:56:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, he's going to go inside of the net to save him.\N{\rEng}嘿 他要进渔网里救那只海狮
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.77,0:56:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, really nice.\N{\rEng}太好了 真的太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.96,0:56:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a relief this time...\N{\rEng}这次可以松一口气了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.39,0:57:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but it highlights the new realities of filming wildlife\N{\rEng}但这也凸显了拍摄野生动物新的实际情况
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.87,0:57:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's changing ocean.\N{\rEng}在如今瞬息万变的海洋中
